raw_data.description: Charlotte Mecklenburg Library is the library system serving Mecklenburg County, NC with 20 locations and a digital online site. Our mission is to improve lives and build a stronger community. We create a community of readers and empower individuals.
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 1.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text: Libreria muy linda, tiene ambiente tranquilo para leer, estudiar sin molestias.

I want to share the wonderful experience I just had at the Hickory Grove Library. I needed books for my neighborhood kids, and Amare (I hope I got her name right) went above and beyond on a Sat eve. She was so kind and so helpful with customer service. My neighborhood kids were happy when they received their books and monthly schedule of library activities, they were unaware of the opportunities available...for free. If you are in the neighborhood, please stop by and say hi. You have very knowledgeable staff just waiting to help you solve a problem...for free.
I went there for an AARP sponsored event.
The worst library to study. Unless you get a room .the place is LOUD. What happened to people whispering in libraries?

This has become one of my young grandchildren's favorite places to go when they spend time with me. There are several computers with educational software, puzzles, and of course, books that can enjoyed there or borrowed to be read at home. It's like being in a candy store for them!

I visited Hickory Grove library on 3-21-25 around 10:30 am. I’m a senior in need of getting something printed from an email sent to me. I hadn’t been to the library for services other than to early vote. Haven’t used a laptop computer in years. I needed help but none offered other than telling me how to get the email printed. I’m not technical at all and shared that with the young lady at the desk. I ended up going to UPS and the young woman there took the time to show me exactly what I needed to do to get my Visa card rebate form printed. I was disappointed.
Very kind and helpful staff this is one of the best libraries in charlotte
Very nice location.  The workers are very helpful.  Love to bring the kids
Un servicio de calidad, realmente un servicio vital para nuestro vecindario.

Really like this library here. It's very informative with a wealth of information available from zoom classes, crafts, writing, food banks (not at this site), free computer classes and more. This site  host the free shower and amenities for those whom choose to use it ( bus service on wheels) . Staff very friendly and helpful. The study or quite room have to be booked the day of use up to 2 hours usage. Very peaceful and calm here. Plenty of natural light and space to read or study.
Beautiful library, with books for all ages
Nice and helpful staff. The internet connection was down when I arrived. It took about 15 minutes to reconnect. Overall, it's a good, quiet place to work on your laptop.
Very clean, quite and friendly staff
Nice little library with friendly staff.
Attended an AARP session. Very nice set up.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for visiting us at Hickory Grove!

reviews_data.review_text: Nice cozy place, come for the books, but skip the internet. I concur its was faster than dialup, but slow enough to make sure you don't learn anything for free. Capped at 60mpb/s. Was quicker to use my phone for internet instead.
Need a better books selections some seemed outdated adult fiction kids area need to be more functional high tech
I had to have some printed copies done today...I know the staff they see me most times...my go to library ❤️🤗

Majority of the librarians are super friendly and helpful and my little one loves it here! Nice sized children's area with little touch screen computers, nice size computer lab and adult area, as well. It isn't big but the quaint size gives it a familial feel. Frequent and they will know you by name and can assist with the type of material you're looking for!

Edited to add: We've been to EVERY branch and these are the best and friendliest librarians!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for supporting the Library, Queen! We are grateful for your patronage and this sweet review. We look forward to seeing you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Wanted to get a card for my kids unfortunately the two women would not stop their conversation to attend to us maybe they should find another job
They have a huge selection of books and a lot of places to sit.
Nice n quiet. Plenty of seats and areas to hold a quiet study area and reading spots
reviews_data.owner_answer: Shana, it means a lot to us that you took time out to review our branch. We hope you'll visit us again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Clean, peaceful and the staff is very helpful.

reviews_data.review_text: Wow, so glad to visit Hickory Grove Branch today!! Everyone there is so very helpful and friendly, special thanks to Michelle for your assistance!  Many thanks to all of you for being there for our community.  Will be back soon!!!
NICE PLACE AND GREAT

I visit libraries often, and give Hickory Grove branch 5 Stars! Staff are always friendly. They speak when you walk in the door and say good-bye when you exit. Very neat, organized and accessible. The fifth star was given when I received a call I’d left my bookmark in a returned book! ❤️

I really  Really appreciate the Neatest place and Areas  inside the Store The  staff and or Volunteers Can be very very very Rude And not Exemplary Encounter Encouragement Experiences when it comes to customer satisfaction and Customer friendliness.
Love the library has all kinds of great books,the staff are nice, and it doesn't take a century to sign up.  I do however wish for there to be more newer manga and comics but overall love the place!
Great library in the Hickory Grove area. Very helpful staff.
Absolutely awesome
Great place, great people, great service!
Le doy 4 estrellas xk siempre la visito y los trabajadores son muy amables y buenos con los clientes  siempre están al pendiente
I enjoy going. The staff is really nice. Lalitia remembers how much I like the pottery class and I know some of the librarians by name.
Friday and Saturday 9 to 5 Monday to Thursday 9 to 8
I love coming here for books the staff is so nice
Friendly staff and quiet place.
is a good place where children learn to read and learn to do other things help a lot
This library has a peaceful environment and shared a variety of information with the public. I tend to feel very out of place in public places but the staff makes me feel right at home.
I love this location. It’s the only location I been to but the staff are always informative and very nice. It’s always clean and the energy is always cool.

workers are helpful they have many fun activities and tutor help fo kids i would only think a library has books but my family comes here practically everyday its so fun weve made dishes from clay learned dancee moves and went to a ukelele concert

I like this library
Clean.Good.Nice staff.Security on duty. Area for kids, teens etc
The lady at the front desk was friendly and very helpful.

Full of good memories! I went to the library everyday to study for my real estate license. There were study rooms and quiet reading rooms available that I frequently used. The staff is friendly and its a nice environment to learn. They have a variety of events on the calendar. Not to mention there is a eclectic selection of books, cds and foreign films available to borrow. Glad I found this location!
Very friendly and helpful staff.....especially kind to my husband when he stops by to pick up my books!
Great place for kids....they have all types of programs for all ages.
Good study environment!

Love the story time for children and activities they schedule throughout the year.  Many thanks to Mr. Malcolm for great story telling and always being so helpful, also Ms. Leah, and the other kind librarians at this great location.
Story time for babies and families are AWESOME!
Great books and polite staff :)
Kind of ghetto but the staff is nice.

(Children's section review)

Parking lot is not very big.
Entrance is nice and the Librarians at the front desk are very nice.
Children books for sale are eight up front. Children's area of the library is big and spacious.
There are benches for sitting, plenty of tables for children to sit at.
They have a small computer area with about 5 computers.
A section full of board books.
A nice section full of easy readers.
Puzzle and bead games.
Large DVD selection.
nice outside area for sitting and having picnics.
Librarian stationed inside children's area for help.
I did not attend a storytime but they have a separate room with glass doors that close to keep kids in during story time.
Helpful people, large stock
Nice & clean. Great spot for kids and adults .
Small, but the children's area is really nice.
Would've been 5 if there were more fine honey's, but its a great library doe 😇.

I am a library patron because I don't feel like it is utilized as often for reading or getting books. But I only use the library computer room because my computer screen is cracked at the moment. But to be spoken to by a older librarian rudely on May 17, 2016 at 3:15pm at the Hickory Grove Library because she doesn't want to do her job is not welcoming or inviting. First she caught a attitude because I brought her my returned books instead of dropping them in the slot out front and then she told me next time " I better" bring my card because I got a temporary pass. I did not plan on coming to use the computer but being in that I am planning an event I wanted to shoot a email to someone and couldn't find my card after going back to my car to double check for it. I do not appreciate being spoken to in that manner. I said thank you and please, I am not a rude person and not one to bad mouth but I will not be talked down to because her conversation about her 72 whatever with the spoiler on the back to security be interrupted. Even though I did not speak but waited for her to notice me but got tired of security glancing at me behind her time and time again. I will not return to this branch again.
I love the  reading room  .
Small branch but friendly staff
